The module `CSCTriggerPrimitivesDQM` in `L1Trigger/CSCTriggerPrimitives` used to function as a (maybe even the?) DQM module for the CSC trigger primitives. Since then, it has been superseded by dedicated modules in `DQM/CSCMonitorModule`. It was enabled in the DQM chain until 2014 at which point it was turned off as explained here: https://github.com/dmitrijus/cmssw/commit/069cc0a00b211ce1bcf8c37600237bfbf9eb0982. It also used to be enabled in test configurations in ` DQM/CSCMonitorModule`. Furthermore, `CSCTriggerPrimitivesDQM` is derived from `CSCTriggerPrimitivesReader` which has the same purpose, namely comparing unpacked ALCT/CLCT/LCT with re-emulated ALCT/CLCT/LCT. 

Part of this project is also to update the `CSCTriggerPrimitivesReader`. That will be done in a future PR.

